Re: ~対象とし、．．．~目標としている
by NileCat » Mon 02.28.2011 3:00 pm Sounds fine to me. Let me try the same thing! And…could you tell me if it sounds weird in English? I am not really sure, especially about the proper use of the articles and singular/plural forms. Also, I'd like to know if my choice of the subject is inappropriate. Thank you!This book is intended for intermediate-level learners of Japanese, and it aims at boosting their ability to an advanced level. NileCat
